race.comment: MONTE VEEBEE (7) first run for the Baker yard on resumption, scored a slick 4 len win over 1250m at Newcastle in sizzling time. Thrown in the deep end today and no reason he can't get the job done again from the good gate. Hard to catch. BUNDEENA (1) consistent sprinter who comes here in peak form. Chased hard with a gallant second over 1200m at this track. Shoulders the big weight again and Rawiller sticks. Will be strong late if they overdo it up front. POLYGLOT (3) handy gelding resuming. Looks primed for this with the two searching trials and can make his presence felt despite not winning past 1100m. Look for him late. UZZIAH (2) tough Newcastle-trained gelding who will stalk the speed with the claim. Stuck on well to run third over 1200m here on resumption. Value contender.  WALLENDA (5) five-weeks between runs when a fairly ordinary fourth to Sovereign Hill over 1250m at Canterbury. Gets a better set-up for this and don't dismiss.
